claim.claim-text:
30. In an etch chamber having a top and a bottom electrode, process gas inlets, and a chuck for holding a wafer, the wafer including a dielectric layer to be etched, a method for curing a photoresist disposed on the wafer, comprising: 
introducing a gas into an etch chamber through a process gas inlet, the gas in the etch chamber defining a curing environment; 
exposing the wafer to the curing environment, the wafer having a developed photoresist layer, the developed photoresist layer being formulated so as to contain a hardening agent; 
interacting the hardening agent with the curing environment; and 
converting a portion of the developed photoresist layer to a hardened layer.
